OOPs:
1- Encapsulation: Encapsulation in Java is a mechanism of wrapping the(variables) and  (methods) together as a single unit.
   -Data Hiding
   //1st way to implement Encapsulation
   1. variables private
   2. setter methods
   3. getter methods

   //2nd Way to implement Encapsulation
    1. variables private
    2. Constructors
    3. getter methods

   //3nd Way to implement Encapsulation
    1. variables private
    2. Constructors- setting the value
    3. getter methods - getting the value
    4. setter methods - Updating the value

    //4th Way to implement Encapsulation
     1. private methods
     2. public methods

Constructor: multiple values
           : initializing the value of a variable

Setter: one value at a time
        Update the value of variable

        WE should not use Setter or Constructor for applying login within it

2- Polymorphism
    -Method Overloading[Done]
    -Method Overriding

3- Inheritance
    -Abstraction
    -Interface